article.headline: Michigan State 71, Oakland 53
article.story: EAST LANSING, Mich. (AP) -- Drew Neitzel's 21 points and a 32-6 first-half blitz powered Michigan State past Oakland 71-53 on Saturday. Neitzel was 8-for-15 from the field and had seven assists for the Spartans (6-1), who shot 59.3 percent before halftime and held the Golden Grizzlies to 22.2 percent accuracy. Marquise Gray had career highs with 14 points and 12 rebounds, Goran Suton added 12 points, and Travis Walton matched his high output with 11. Vova Severovas led Oakland (4-3) with 13 points and six rebounds. Derick Nelson, a Lansing native, had 12 points in his homecoming. Michigan State led 8-7 when it found the range and denied Oakland any decent opportunities. A 22-10 rebound advantage in the first 20 minutes added to the cushion. The Grizzlies trimmed a 27-point deficit to 15 early in the second half, only to see the margin grow again until the closing minutes. The Spartans finished with edges of 43-28 in rebounds and 19-5 in assists, as Oakland showed the effects of a rugged road swing. The Grizzlies are approaching the middle of a 12-game stretch that has them playing away from home 11 times.
